libscrypt
------------------------------------------
Linux scrypt shared library.

Full credit to algorithm designer and example code from Colin Percival here:
http://www.tarsnap.com/scrypt.html

Utilises BASE64 encoding library from ISC.

Official project page, including stable tarballs found here:
http://www.lolware.net/libscrypt.html

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.4.1-1
  libscrypt-devel-1.21-1bl1
  libscrypt0-1.21-1bl1
  libssp0-4.9.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-4
  cygport-0.20.2-1
  gcc-core-4.9.3-1
  libtool-2.4.6-2
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/technion/libscrypt/

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/technion/libscrypt/archive/v1.21.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libscrypt-1.21-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libscrypt-1.21-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libscrypt-1.21-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libscrypt-1.21-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libscrypt0-1.21-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libscrypt-devel-1.21-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libscrypt)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libscrypt.README
  /usr/share/doc/libscrypt/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/libscrypt/README.md

(libscrypt0)
  /usr/bin/cygscrypt-0.dll

(libscrypt-devel)
  /usr/include/libscrypt.h
  /usr/lib/libscrypt.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libscrypt.pc

